pullRequest.body:
Remove `structure BilinForm` from `LinearAlgebra/BilinearForm/Basic` and migrate all of `_root_.BilinForm` to `LinearMap.BilinForm`

Closes: #10553 

This isn't the end of the story, as there's still a lot of overlap between `LinearAlgebra/BilinearForm` and `LinearAlgebra/SesquilinearForm` but that can be sorted out in subsequent PRs.

Supersedes: 

- #11057
- #11032
- #10432
- #10422

---

This looks good to me, thanks! I think probably it would be a waste of time to deprecate most of this; but we should deprecated `BilinForm` itself so that it's obvious that the replacement is `LinearMap.BilinForm`.

I think there's still a lot of cleanup to do after this PR, but it probably makes sense to avoid this one growing too much.

Thank you for doing this! Please apply my suggestions and feel free to merge

Indeed there is still a lot of clean up to follow but I agree it can happen separately.

bprs d+

**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion {B : BilinForm R M} (hB : B.IsRefl) : (a • B).IsRefl := fun x y => ```

**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion {B : BilinForm R M} (hB : B.IsSymm) : (a • B).IsSymm := fun x y => ```

**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion {B : BilinForm R M} (hB : B.IsAlt) : (a • B).IsAlt := fun x => ```
The `toFun` shouldn't be needed here.

```
theorem toLin'_apply (A : BilinForm R M) (x : M) : toLinHom A x = A x :=
  rfl
```
gives me:
```
function expected at
  toLinHom
term has type
  BilinForm ?m.30887 ?m.30888 →ₗ[?m.30887] ?m.30888 →ₗ[?m.30887] ?m.30888 →ₗ[?m.30887] ?m.30887
```
Similarly for `⇑(toLinHom A x) = A x`
Try adding an explicit type annotation to `toLinHom`
Thanks, I've replaced the other additions of `toFun` with explicit type annotations as well.

Can you add a TODO comment in this docstring that indicates a lot of the file is now pointless (for instance, `toLinHom` is now the identity!).

I don't think we should delete any of these definitions to fix that in this PR, but it would be good to record that the file needs further work to avoid confused readers.
Done.
This is `restrictScalars12` combined with `compr2` I think
Done, thanks.
Can you leave behind a `@[deprecated] alias` for `_root_.BilinForm`?

I tried adding:
```
@[deprecated] alias _root_.BilinForm := LinearMap.BilinForm
```
but then `open LinearMap (BilinForm)` no longer seems to work - I have to replace every `BilinForm` with `LinearMap.BilinForm`.

Perhaps a better idea then is `export LinearMap (BilinForm)` at the top of the file, which means that any old code that uses `BilinForm` resolves it to `LinearMap.BilinForm` automatically (with no deprecation).
Okay, done.
I think you can replace this with `:= A x`!

```
def toLinHomAux₁ (A : BilinForm R M) (x : M) : M →ₗ[R] R := A x
```
gives me
```
type mismatch
  (fun x y ↦ (A x) y) x
has type
  M → R : Type (max u_1 u_2)
but is expected to have type
  M →ₗ[R] R : Type (max u_2 u_1)
```

I've changed the proof of `toLinHom` so that it no longer depends on `toLinHomAux₁`. However, this PR introduces a dependency on `toLinHomAux₁` in `BilinearForm/Orthogonal` so I can't remove it altogether yet.
I found a solution using a local attribute
Thanks.
This one is now `:= A`!
Yes, that one works.
I think this instance is dangerous; it applies even when the `BilinForm` alias is not being used, and is what breaks `A x` in the other comment thread in this PR.

Even with this instance in place, the lemmas below are pretty useless; you get things like
```
coe_smul : (fun x y ↦ ((a • B) x) y) = a • fun x y ↦ (B x) y
```
Okay, I've removed that instance. Thanks.
This should be `noaligned`
Done, thanks.
I think `inferInstance` would be better here.
Done, here and elsewhere.

Let's soften the wording a bit here:
```suggestion
A lot of this file is now redundant following the replacement of the dedicated `_root_.BilinForm`
```

```suggestion
`LinearMap.BilinForm.toLinHom` is now just the identity map. This redundant code should be removed.
```

```suggestion

@[deprecated] --  2024-04-08
abbrev BilinForm (R M : Type*) [CommSemiring R] [AddCommMonoid M] [Module R M] := M →ₗ[R] M →ₗ[R] R

```
@ocfnash  I tried that before, but it seems to conflict with `open LinearMap (BilinForm)` https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/11278#discussion_r1536821607 so we abandoned that idea.
Fair enough.

These lemma statements are now a bit weird, since they only talk about one layer of coercion.

I think probably the thing to do is just deprecate all of the `coe_` lemmas in this file in a follow-up PR; I think there probably just isn't a useful version of these any more, especially since the `LinearMap` ones can take over anyway.
Agreed.

There's loads of cleanup to do (and I am hoping @mans0954 will generously continue to take an interest in this worthy project) but I think the important thing to do is to get the definition deleted: that way the problem can only shrink.

> I think probably the thing to do is just deprecate all of the `coe_` lemmas in this file in a follow-up PR

I've done a PR for this #12112 - in fact it seems most of that file can be deprecated.
